es.utils.mapper

Class Mapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • es.utils.mapper.Mapper

  • public class Mapper
extends Object
    This class handle a set of mapping between two objects. It is the central part of the mapping logic and allow the user to create multiple mappings easily.
    Author:
    eschoysman
    See Also:
    MapperObject, ClassMapper, DirectMapper, EnumMapper

      • add

        public <T,U> Mapper add(Class<T> from,
                        Class<U> to)
                 throws MappingException
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the source object
        U - the type of the destination object Allow to add a default mapping between type T and U.
        T - type of the input object
        U - type of the destination object
        Parameters:
        from - type of the input object
        to - type of the destination object
        Returns:
        this Mapper instance
        Throws:
        MappingException - in the following cases:
        • one between from and to is null
        • one between from and to is a interface type
        • to does not have an empty constructor
